{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti Chapter 12 does not specify a particular number of hells.**\n\nIt refers to sinners obtaining \"dreadful hells\" (Mn_12.54, 12.75, 12.76)[^1] and gives examples—Tamisra (\"such as Tamisra and the others,\" Mn_12.75), Asipatravana (\"the Asipatravana and the like,\" Mn_12.75), and Kumbhīpāka (\"the dreadful Kumbhipaka hells,\" Mn_12.76)—but provides no explicit count or full list there.[^2] A numbered list of 21 hells appears instead in Chapter 4 (beginning at Mn_4.87).[^3]\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12, paragraph p-074f6e](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-074f6e).\n\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12, paragraphs p-074f6e](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-074f6e).\n\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 4, [paragraph p-8b8ea4](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/04/translation/#p-8b8ea4).",
